{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddcf858f1-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s2810"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2810"},"text":"§ 2810.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Disclosure by Secretary; commencement, scope, etc.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Beginning with data for calendar year 1980, the Secretary shall make publicly available data in the Secretary’s possession for each mortgagee which is not otherwise subject to the requirements of this chapter and which is not exempt pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2805/b"},"text":"section 2805(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" (and for each mortgagee making mortgage loans exempted under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2803/g"},"text":"section 2803(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":"), with respect to mortgage loans approved (or for which completed applications are received) by the Secretary for insurance under title I or II of the National Housing Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1702"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 1702","children":[],"tail":" et seq., 1707 et seq.]. Such data to be disclosed shall consist of data comparable to the data which would be disclosed if such mortgagee were subject to the requirements of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2803"},"text":"section 2803 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Disclosure statements containing data for each such mortgagee for a primary metropolitan statistical area, metropolitan statistical area, or consolidated metropolitan statistical area that is not comprised of designated primary metropolitan statistical areas shall, at a minimum, be publicly available at the central depository of data established pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2803/f"},"text":"section 2803(f) of this title","children":[],"tail":" for such primary metropolitan statistical area, metropolitan statistical area, or consolidated metropolitan statistical area that is not comprised of designated primary metropolitan statistical areas. The Secretary shall also compile and make publicly available aggregate data for such mortgagees by census tract, and tables indicating aggregate lending patterns, in a manner comparable to the information required to be made publicly available in accordance with "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2809"},"text":"section 2809 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddcf858f2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/200/tIII/s311"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–200, title III, § 311","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/399/tIII/s340/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–399, title III, § 340(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-08"},"text":"Oct. 8, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1658"},"text":"94 Stat. 1658","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/181/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–181, title I","children":[],"tail":" [title VII, § 701(a)], "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-11-30"},"text":"Nov. 30, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/1266"},"text":"97 Stat. 1266","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/242/tV/s565/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–242, title V, § 565(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-02-05"},"text":"Feb. 5, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1945"},"text":"101 Stat. 1945","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/tXII/s1211/c/2/D"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, title XII, § 1211(c)(2)(D)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/525"},"text":"103 Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddcf858f3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddcf858f4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddcf858f5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The National Housing Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-27/ch847"},"text":"act June 27, 1934, ch. 847","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/1246"},"text":"48 Stat. 1246","children":[],"tail":". Titles I and II of the Act are classified generally to subchapters I (§ 1702 et seq.) and II (§ 1707 et seq.), respectively, of chapter 13 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1701"},"text":"section 1701 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddcf858f6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(or for which completed applications are received)” after “approved”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/242"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–242","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(and for each mortgagee making mortgage loans exempted under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2803/g"},"text":"section 2803(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":")” after “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2805/b"},"text":"section 2805(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/181"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–181","children":[],"tail":" substituted “primary metropolitan statistical area, metropolitan statistical area, or consolidated metropolitan statistical area that is not comprised of designated primary metropolitan statistical areas” for “standard metropolitan statistical areas” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddcf858f7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"iddcf858f8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1989 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73","children":[],"tail":" applicable to each calendar year beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1989","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/s1211/k"},"text":"section 1211(k) of Pub. L. 101–73","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2802"},"text":"section 2802 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note",